= Biography

== About Myself
I am a Research Scientist at Facebook. Previously, I was a PhD Candidate in Mechanical Engineering at UC Berkeley, working with [https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~tomlin/ Professor Claire J. Tomlin] in the [http://hybrid.eecs.berkeley.edu/ Hybrid Systems Laboratory]. Also, I was affiliated with the [http://bair.berkeley.edu/ Berkeley Artificial Intelligence Research Lab (BAIR)]. I am interested in modeling and control of Cyber-Physical Systems using Applied Machine Learning and Statistical Learning. Please take a look at my [projects.html projects] and [publications.html publications] that are at the intersection of control theory, computer science, and economics, with applications to electricity markets.

== Education
I have obtained the following academic degrees:
- PhD in Mechanical Engineering, [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley], December 2018
- MA in Mathematics, [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley], May 2018
- MS in Mechanical Engineering, [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley], May 2017
- MS in Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences (EECS), [https://www.berkeley.edu/ UC Berkeley], May 2016
- BS in Mechanical Engineering, [https://www.tum.de/en/homepage/ Technische Universität München] (Germany), February 2014

During the Fall 2016 semester I was a visiting student in the [https://lids.mit.edu/ Laboratory for Information and Decision Systems] (LIDS) at MIT, supervised by [https://dahleh.lids.mit.edu/ Prof. Munther A. Dahleh] and [https://mardavij.lids.mit.edu/ Dr. Mardavij Roozbehani].

